id: pm-fu5d
title: "Dogfood 2026-05-21 follow-ups: test --add key validation, semantic-fallback labeling, close active-children info, stale blocker on close"
description: "Manual dogfood findings not yet fixed (separate from pm-5k2w which holds the 2026-05-20 polish backlog). B2 [med]: pm test --add 'cmd=...,name=...' silently stores the whole pair as the command - reject/warn unknown keys, accept cmd as alias for command. S1 [med]: when no embedding provider is configured but ollama auto-defaults engage, search reports mode:semantic with no warning even though embedded_items=0 - clarify degraded/lexical state. C3 [med]: closing a parent/epic with active children under minimal governance is silent - emit an informational closed_with_active_children warning even when not blocking. C4 [low]: closed items retain blocked_by metadata - clear/annotate on terminal transition. U2 [low]: did-you-mean missing for unknown options (--statuss). U3 [low]: accept --list as alias for --explore on package/extension. CAL1 [med]: support compound relative event times (start=+1d,end=+1d+2h) or a duration= field."
type: Chore
status: open
priority: 3
tags[3]: agent-ux,dogfood,polish
created_at: "2026-05-21T21:57:44.257Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-23T04:07:43.531Z"
assignee: claude-code-agent
author: claude-code-agent
acceptance_criteria: Each listed finding is fixed or explicitly deferred with rationale; no agent-blocking introduced.
parent: pm-rnpb
comments[5]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-23T03:50:38.508Z",claude-code-agent,"C3 + C4 FIXED (pm-uz25 step 2) in src/cli/commands/close.ts. C3: active-children are now scanned even under minimal governance; off-mode close emits an informational closed_with_active_children:<id>:<children> warning (never blocks), distinct from the warn/strict close_validation_active_children. C4: terminal close now clears the stale active blocker — scalar blocked_by + blocked_reason and any blocked_by dependency edges (preserving the pm-kyd6 scalar/graph invariant) — and annotates with closed_cleared_blocked_by:<id>:<previousBlocker>. 2 regression tests added; close-command.spec 11/11 green. Remaining fu5d items: U2/U3 (me, next), S1/B2 (query-ux sub-agent), CAL1 (calendar-ux sub-agent)."
  "2026-05-23T03:55:05.807Z",claude-code-agent,"U2 + U3 FIXED (pm-uz25 step 3). U2 (did-you-mean for --statuss): the unknown-option suggestion + never-block typo-normalization infra already existed, but LIST_FILTER_FLAG_CONTRACTS was missing --status (the only list flag absent vs `pm list --help`). Added { flag: '--status' } so `pm list --statuss open` now auto-corrects to --status (flag_typo, high confidence) exactly like every other list flag. U3: added `--list` as an alias for `--explore` on package/extension (register-setup.ts: option + readBoolean('explore','list'); cli-contracts EXTENSION_FLAG_CONTRACTS += --list). Verified: `pm package --list` / `pm extension --list` => action:explore. Tests: bootstrap-args.spec U2 case + cli.integration.spec U3 case, both green."
  "2026-05-23T03:57:09.584Z",query-ux-subagent,"query-ux-subagent START: implementing S1 (search degraded labeling) + B2 (test --add cmd alias + unknown-key validation)."
  "2026-05-23T04:00:36.580Z",query-ux-subagent,"query-ux-subagent DONE: S1 + B2 implemented, type-check clean, focused specs 73/73 green.\n\nS1 (search degraded/lexical labeling) — src/cli/commands/search.ts:\n- computeSemanticOrHybridHits now returns { hits, embeddedItems } (was SearchHit[]). embeddedItems = semanticScores.size (count of docs that actually matched the vector/embedding corpus). New SemanticQueryResult interface added.\n- In runSearch main flow, after a SUCCESSFUL built-in semantic/hybrid run (no fallback thrown), if embeddedItems === 0 we push warning: search_${effectiveMode}_degraded:no_embedded_items:results_are_lexical -> i.e. 'search_semantic_degraded:no_embedded_items:results_are_lexical' and 'search_hybrid_degraded:no_embedded_items:results_are_lexical'. Reported mode is intentionally UNCHANGED (stays semantic/hybrid) per spec; only the warning makes the degraded/lexical state observable. Ranking/threshold/limit/projection untouched. Never errors (additive warning only). Distinct from the pre-existing search_<mode>_fallback:* warnings (which fire when the backend throws/degrades to keyword).\n- Note: the empty-CORPUS path (items exist, semantic ran, 0 vector matches) is separate from the empty-RESULTSET early-return (filteredDocuments.length===0) which still legitimately reports mode without a warning.\n\nB2 (test --add cmd alias + unknown-key validation) — src/cli/commands/test.ts:\n- looksLikeStructuredLinkedTestEntry regex now includes 'cmd'.\n- Added STRUCTURED_LINKED_TEST_ADD_KEYS allowlist (command, cmd, path, scope, timeout, timeout_seconds, pm_context_mode, env_set, env_clear, shared_host_safe, assert_stdout_contains, assert_stdout_regex, assert_stderr_contains, assert_stderr_regex, assert_stdout_min_lines, assert_json_field_equals, assert_json_field_gte, note) + normalizeStructuredAddEntry().\n- parseAddEntries now runs structured kv through normalizeStructuredAddEntry: throws PmCliError(USAGE) on any unknown key — message: '--add does not recognize key(s) \"<key>\". Allowed keys: command, cmd, path, ...'. Folds cmd->command; if both command and cmd given and differ, throws '--add command and cmd must match when both are provided'. Bare commands (incl. those containing = like '--reporter=dot') still pass through unchanged.\n- Fixes the original bug where 'cmd=...,name=...' was silently stored verbatim as the command.\n\nTests added:\n- tests/unit/test-command.spec.ts: 3 new it() blocks — cmd alias maps to command; unknown key (name/bogus) and command/cmd conflict rejected (USAGE) with nothing stored; bare command containing = preserved.\n- tests/unit/search-command.spec.ts: 2 new it() blocks — empty embedding corpus (ext vector adapter returns []) emits the degraded warning for both semantic and hybrid; non-empty corpus does NOT emit it.\n\nVerification: npx tsc --noEmit -p tsconfig.json => clean (exit 0). PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 run-tests.mjs test (both specs) => Test Files 2 passed, Tests 73 passed.\n\nShared/forbidden files I did NOT touch but recommend the coordinator update:\n1. CHANGELOG.md [Unreleased] entry (suggested text below).\n2. src/cli/commands/completion.ts and/or contracts: if --add key completions are enumerated anywhere, add 'cmd'. (I did not verify whether they enumerate these keys — coordinator should grep for the existing key list e.g. 'shared_host_safe' in completion/contracts/docs.)\n3. docs: any 'pm test --add' reference doc should mention the cmd alias and that unknown keys now error.\n\nSuggested CHANGELOG [Unreleased] lines:\n- Added: 'pm search --mode semantic|hybrid' now emits a 'search_<mode>_degraded:no_embedded_items:results_are_lexical' warning when the embedding corpus is empty, so agents can tell results are effectively lexical even though mode stays semantic/hybrid.\n- Added: 'pm test --add' accepts 'cmd' as an alias for 'command'.\n- Fixed: 'pm test --add' now errors on unknown keys (e.g. name=) instead of silently storing the whole 'cmd=...,name=...' string as the command."
  "2026-05-23T04:07:43.531Z",calendar-ux-subagent,"calendar-ux-subagent: CAL1 (duration= on --event) is done as part of pm-uzmf. duration=<relative> (e.g. duration=2h, duration=+1d) now derives event end from startAt in both parse sites (pm create parseEvents and pm update parseEventEntries). end + duration are mutually exclusive. Units are h/d/w/m where m=MONTHS (no minutes token). See pm-uzmf comment for full details and test coverage.\n"
body: ""
